title: Darwin put on tropical cyclone warning
description: A cyclone warning has been issued for Darwin as Tropical Cyclone Fina moves towards the Top End coast.

title: ASX down almost two per cent at the open
description: The local share market opened sharply lower at almost two per cent on Friday morning, following a huge sell-off on Wall Street overnight.

title: Lefties Losing It: Hate, fear and hysterics
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi has reacted to the left’s latest hate, fear and hysterics.

title: Albanese ‘secretly pleased’ Australia missed out on hosting COP31
description: Sky News host James Macpherson weighs in on Australia conceding defeat to Turkey in the bid to host COP31 in 2026.   “Now overall, I think maybe Anthony Albanese might be kind of secretly pleased that we’re not hosting this,” Mr Macpherson said.  “Chris Bowen, did you hear? He talked about how, but don’t worry, it’s not all bad news because Australia will have, I will have all the power in terms of facilitating the climate negotiations.  “Chris Bowen still gets something out of it.”

title: Meghan Markle brutally roasted for boldly claiming it’s ‘brave’ to sell jam
description: Meghan Markle has been brutally mocked for claiming it’s ‘brave’ of her to sell jam.   The Duchess of Sussex made the claim in an interview with Harper’s Bazaar.   The Duchess was asked about what she hopes her children will learn from watching her navigate being a working mother.   “I hope they see the value of being brave,” The Duchess said.   “They saw it when the jam was just a pot on the stove, bubbling.”  “When you’re young, I think you are a little bit more fearless. As we get older, we lose some of that.”  Fans have taken to social media to blast her for the comments.

title: Vladimir Putin gets surprise performance from dancing robot
description: Sky News host Freya Leach reacts to a robot dancing for Russian President Vladimir Putin during an AI conference in Moscow.   “A couple of weeks ago, we covered this story of a robot that fell on its face,” Ms Leach said.   “The developers have been busy, and they have, I guess, fixed the bug … and now it’s been presented to Putin.   “It’s evolved from sleepy Joe to dancing Trump rallies with the little dance.”

title: CNBC forced to reveal Trump’s economic triumphs
description: CNBC was in shock presenting the latest jobs figures coming out of the US under President Trump.

title: Leavitt clashes with reporter over Ukraine-Russia peace plan
description: White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt has sparred with a reporter over claims the Trump administration's Ukraine peace plan demands major concessions from Kyiv.  During Thursday's press briefing, a reporter pressed Leavitt on whether Russia had been involved in drafting the proposal, saying sources described the plan as requiring "major concessions from Ukraine" and "not much from Russia".  Leavitt rejected that outright.  "Your understanding is wrong. Have you read the full plan? You haven't," she snapped back.  "You've read reporting from one side of the war."  She insisted the administration has spoken "equally with both sides," adding that President Trump, his national security team, envoy Elliot Witkoff and Secretary Marco Rubio have all engaged directly with both Kyiv and Moscow.  Leavitt said Witkoff and Rubio met Ukrainian officials again in the past week to discuss the proposal, which she called "a good plan for both Russia and Ukraine."  The clash came as two people familiar with the talks told reporters the US has signalled to President Zelenskyy that Ukraine may have to give up territory and surrender some weapons as part of the draft framework.  They requested anonymity due to the sensitivity of the discussions.

title: Homer Simpsons invade Santa Monica in wild Fortnite flash mob
description: Sky News contributor Joe Hildebrand reacts to a flock of Homer Simpsons taking over Santa Monica as part of a promotional stunt with the video game Fortnite.  “It’s very difficult to know how to place this in context because there is no context,” Mr Hildebrand said.  “Basically, The Simpsons is a massive character in a … video game named Fortnite, and now there’s a flock of Homers in Santa Monica.  “A bunch of real-life Homer Simpsons decided to do a flash mob.”

title: Donald Trump savages 'no talent' Jimmel Kimmel calling him a 'bum'
description: US President Donald Trump has called for late-night host Jimmy Kimmel to be pulled off the air.  The attack came from the president's Truth Social account, where he called Kimmel a "bum".  "Why does ABC Fake News keep Jimmy Kimmel, a man with NO TALENT and VERY POOR TELEVISION RATINGS, on the air? Why do the TV Syndicates put up with it? Also, totally biased coverage. Get the bum off the air!!!" Trump wrote.  Trump was responding to the comedian's latest monologue, where he went on the offensive against the president over the Epstein files.  Kimmel began his attack by calling the situation "Hurricane Epstein"

title: ARIA Awards winner jokes she is new Australian PM, says all immigrants welcome
description: Sky News host James Macpherson reacts to singer Amy Taylor declaring herself as the new prime minister during an acceptance speech at the ARIA Awards.  “Just because you play the guitar well does not make you a philosopher,” Mr Macpherson said.   “We’ve got a big job to educate our younger generation, that’s for sure.”

title: ‘GREAT GUY’: Trump post hilarious AI video with Cristiano Ronaldo
description: US President Donald Trump has posted a hilarious AI-generated video to his Truth Social account.  The video showed himself and the Portuguese sporting superstar Cristiano Ronaldo kicking a ball in the Oval Office.  The video was generated from a photo of Ronaldo's visit to the White House.  The White House’s official X page also posted a video of both men, labelling them “two GOATS”.

title: ‘Ready to serve the people of NSW’: Kellie Sloane elected NSW Liberal Leader
description: The incoming NSW Liberal Leader, Kellie Sloane, addressed the media to outline her vision for the state.  “This has been an uninspiring Labor government, and we are committed to a positive, to a bold and ambitious vision for New South Wales,” Ms Sloane said.   “The Coalition under my leadership will work relentlessly for families.”

title: Zelensky receives draft 28-point plan from Trump containing major concessions for Ukraine
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky has received a draft peace proposal from US President Donald Trump.  The US President produced the 28-point plan with Russia in a bid to end the conflict.  But Europe is insisting it must be involved in future talks, after Kyiv confirmed it has received the newly drafted plan from the US

title: ‘So typical’: Flag-covered bus fails to display Australian flag in careless attempt at unity
description: Sky News host Andrew Bolt reacts to images of a bus in Melbourne displaying three separate flags, none of which is the Australian flag.   “A bus from Melbourne’s Casey council … decorated on both sides by every flag, except the Australian one,” Mr Bolt said.  “So typical.”
